<script type="text/template" id="transcriber-herbarium-widget-template">
  <div class="left">
    <div class="input_field">
      <input type="text" placeholder="" />
      <a href="#" class="btn ok">ok</a>
      <a href="#" class="btn error">!</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="right">
    <a href="#" class="skip">Skip this field</a>
    <a href="#" class="step"></a>
    <a href="#" class="btn finish">Finish this record</a>
  </div>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="closer-template">
  <a href="#" class="close"></a>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="popup-template">
  <div class="content">
    <p>Welcome to the SERNEC Herbarium collections on Notes from Nature and thank you for helping us transcribe specimen records.</p>
    <p>One of the key ways of storing plant material in natural history collections is through herbarium sheets.  These sheets are wonderful for imagining because when plant specimens are prepared, the result is essentially 2-dimensional.</p>
    <p>The imagining gurus working on the SERNEC project have imaged hundreds of thousands of these sheets.   Each sheet contains a plant specimen and a label that contains the species name, locality information and date collected - the who, where and when that is critical for use of these specimens to map biodiversity and its change. All we need is to get those data in usable form.</p>
    <p>You can help us unlock these data for use biodiversity scientists by first finding the label, selecting it via a click-and-drag, and then helping to enter the label content via a step-by-step transcription process that is explained in more detail once you enter the collection. We appreciate your help!</p>
    <button>Got it. Let me transcribe!</button>
  </div>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="highlight-template">
  <a href="#" class="close"></a>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="helper-template">
  <div class="title"></div>
  <div class="description"></div>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="launcher-template">
  <span>Click and drag a square around the specimen label, then click &quot;Start this Record&quot;</span> 
  <a href="#" class="example" data-src="images/sernac.png">See example</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn start hidden">Start this record</a>
  <a href="#" class="skip">Skip this record</a>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="date-input-template">
  <div class="date_field month"><input type="text" name="month" class="month" placeholder="month" /></div> 
  <div class="date_field day"><input type="text" name="day" class="day" placeholder="day" /></div> 
  <div class="date_field year"><input type="text" name="year" class="year" placeholder="year" /></div>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="tooltip-error-template">
  <strong class="title">{{title}}</strong>
  <div class="description">{{description}}</div>
  <div class="tip"></div>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="tooltip-step-template">
  <ul>
    {{#links}}
    <li><a href="#">{{title}}</a></li>
    {{/links}}
  </ul>
  <div class="tip"></div>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="tooltip-template">
  <strong class="title">{{ title }}</strong>
  <div class="description">{{{ description }}}</div>

  <div class="buttons">
    <a href="#" class="btn main">{{ main }}</a> 
    <a href="#" class="btn secondary">{{ secondary }}</a>
  </div>

  <div class="tip"></div>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="tooltip-example-template">
  <div class="buttons"><a href="#/archives/Herbarium" class="btn main">{{ main }}</a></div> 
  <div class="tip"></div>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="statusbar-template">
  <div class="left">
    <h1 class="title">{{ title }}</h1>
    <h3 class="description">{{ description }}</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="right">

    <div class="separator"></div>

    <div class="count">
      <div class="counter">0</div>
      <strong>Records done</strong>
    </div>

    <div class="separator"></div>

    <div class="off">
      <a href="/" class="btn close"></a>
    </div>

  </div>
</script>
